To run the bacteria_bomb.py script, an integrated develpment environemnt (IDE) is needed, therefore, Anaconda python package is reccomended to be installed.
Save all the files within the Assignment_two folder in a folder on the desktop.
Access the command prompt from the windows explorer search bar (Window's user) or terminal (MAC users) and type in spyder followed by the enter key.
Open bacteria_bomb within syper.
Run the code by selecting the run button from the run tab or the green arrow icon (7th icon from the start).
Once ran, the model should produce a density graph presenting the x and y coordinates of the 5000 bacterial agents.
